President Muhammadu Buhari yesterday said his administration was focused on discovering solutions to the utilisation of clean sources of energy. He said he was interested in technologies that will lead to such industrialisation. The President spoke at the Nigeria-Africa natural resources and energy investment summit, with the theme: Towards a greener Africa in Abuja.   SON, Dangote advises block moulders, artisans on standard     One dead as okada ban takes off in Lagos     2023 president: It’s South’s turn after Buhari, says Ayade   The President was represented by the Minister of Mines and Steel Development, Olamilekan Adegbite. He said: “The Nigeria-Africa Natural Resources and Energy Investment Summit (NAFNIS) will convene the African mining, finance, power/energy, oil and gas sectors to chart a way forward for the development of natural resources and energy projects in a sustainable and climate-friendly manner. “With the world focused on discovering and utilising clean sources of energy in order to cut down carbon emissions to protect the world from further climate change.” Adegbite said the joint meeting would support the formulation of favourable policies and strategies for the development of the natural resources sector.